Updated `content/papers/theory.2.md` with minimal structural QA edits only.

Summary of changes:
- Fixed malformed citation syntax to clean markdown footnote form where footnotes exist:
  - `[^4]^,^[^5]` → `[^4][^5]`
  - `^8-10^` → `[^8][^9][^10]`
  - `^14,15^` → `[^14][^15]`
  - `^18,19^` → `[^18][^19]`
  - `^20^` → `[^20]`
  - `^21,22^` → `[^21][^22]`
  - `^14^` and `^19^` cases normalized to footnotes.
- Normalized remaining non-footnote superscript-style numeric citations into plain bracketed references (e.g., `[27]`, `[30,31]`) so markdown renders cleanly.
- Added explicit equation tags for unambiguous `Eq./Eqs.` references:
  - `\tag{7.6}`, `\tag{7.14}`, `\tag{13.10}`, `\tag{13.14}`, `\tag{15.5}`, `\tag{15.7}`, `\tag{16.5}`, `\tag{17.8}`, `\tag{17.17}`.
- Added blank-line paragraph separation around the inline figure placeholder in the “Information Game” section for cleaner markdown structure.

Self-check:
- Paragraph break formatting touched in edited area is blank-line separated.
- Explicit in-text `Eq./Eqs.` references now resolve to tagged display equations in this document, except `Eq. (2.24)`, which is an external reference (from another paper/footnote context), not a missing local equation.
